FBIS4-8852 "dreeu075_i_94012" FBIS-EEU-94-075 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Muslims Firing From `Fortresses' LD1904084294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 0809 GMT 19 Apr 94 LD1904084294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] Cajnice, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- Srpska republic army positions on the right bank of the Drina River have been under fierce Muslim fire from Gorazde since yesterday, despite the cease-fire agreement signed by Radovan Karadzic and Yasushi Akashi two days ago, the command of the Herzegovina Corps reports. [passage omitted] Serb military sources point out that all residential buildings in Gorazde, including the buildings of international humanitarian organizations, are in fact fortresses from which fire is being directed toward Serb positions. [passage omitted]
